article.title: Performance Limits of Solutions to Network Utility Maximization Problems

multiple_choice_question.text: Figure 1 shows the network utility as a function of the power budget. What does the transition point on the graph represent?
choices: The point where the utility function reaches its maximum value.
The point where increasing the power budget by orders of magnitude brings significant gains in utility.
The point where the network transitions from a noise-limited regime to an interference-limited regime.
The point where the utility function starts to decrease.

multiple_choice_question.text: Figure 2 depicts the energy efficiency as a function of the power budget. What trend does the energy efficiency generally follow as the power budget increases?
choices: The energy efficiency remains relatively constant.
